duces a Lie ideal by taking the sum of all `sl₂` subalgebras corresponding to roots\nwhose linear forms lie in `q`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Weights/IsSimple.html#LieAlgebra.IsKilling.invtSubmoduleToLieIdeal","kind":"def","line":236,"name":"LieAlgebra.IsKilling.invtSubmoduleToLieIdeal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Weights/IsSimple.lean#L236-L261"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Lie.Weights.RootSystem","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.RootSystem.Finite.Lemmas"],"instances":[{"className":"RootPairing.IsIrreducible","name":"LieAlgebra.IsKilling.instIsIrreducibleSubtypeWeightMemLieSubalgebraFinsetRootDualRootSystemOfIsSimple","typeNames":["LieAlgebra.IsKilling.rootSystem"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Algebra.Lie.Weights.IsSimple"}